 java
class Box {
    int value;                  // a field (data) inside the object
}

public class S2 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Box b = new Box();      // make a Box object
        b.value = 10;           // set its field 
        System.out.println(b.value); // 10
    }
}
* new Box() creates an object. * b is a **reference** pointing to that object. * b.value reaches inside it. ---
